# Editor Features

## What are the main features and capabilities of the Author Website Editor?

The Author Website Editor’s goal is to empower non-technical authors to quickly build a website for their profession / brand, based in premade page templates and section templates, with the possibility for customization through left slide-in panels:

Focused on primary target audience \- genres (Romance, Fantasy, Mystery / Crime).

* Design Panel (opens the slide-in panel on the left when clicking the Design button on header \- “Customize your site’s appearance”)  
  * Template (clicking on this will open an inner slide-in with template thumbnails)  
    * Template name and thumbnail preview  
      * When clicking in the thumbnail it updates in realtime on the right canvas  
        * sections layouts  
        * color palette  
        * typography

    * Save and Cancel Buttons on the button of the slide-in (fixed)  
  * Colors  (clicking on this will open an inner slide-in with color palettes representation with colors circles)  
    * Presets tab (with color palettes options listed)  
      * Charcoal  
      * Ink  
      * Mist  
      * …  
    * Custom tab  
      * Main color  
      * Website colors  
  * Fonts  
    * Presets tab  
      * Fonts pairing premade options  
      * Custom  
        * Headings  
        * Paragraphs and buttons  
  * Buttons  
    * Style  
      * Filled tab  
        * Roundness  
          * Sharp  
          * Rounded  
          * Pill shape  
      * Outlined tab  
        * Roundness  
          * Sharp  
          * Rounded  
          * Pill shape  
* Settings Panel (opens the slide-in panel on the left when clicking the Settings button on header \- “Configure advanced settings”)  
  * Domains (clicking on this will open an inner slide-in with options)  
    * Connect a domain you own  
    * Edit button  
  * Privacy (“Control your site's privacy.”)  
    * Site Visibility  
      * Public  
      * Hidden  
      * Password protected  
  * Search Engine Optimization  
    * Pages  
      * Meta title  
      * URL Slug  
      * Meta description  
      * Social media image  
    * Books  
    * Blog Posts  
  * Browser icon

The Editor Canvas is a realtime canvas where users can: (after clicking a button on the header):

![][image15]

* The page template modal is structured as follows:  
  * Left sidebar with categories in tabs / links  
  * Right content area where will appear an “html preview” of the page (and NOT a thumbnail image)  
    * the html previews are small scaled html which will change dynamically if for example website styles will change:  
      * color palette  
      * font family changes  
      * etc…
